1. Created an `IdleTimeoutViewModel` to track user activity and manage timeout state
2. Added a custom modifier to detect user interactions across the app
3. Integrated timeout checks in MainActivity's UI hierarchy
4. Added automatic redirection when timeout occurs
5. Reset timer on any user interaction

The timer will automatically reset whenever:
- User touches any part of the screen
- User performs any click/long press/double tap
- Any other pointer interaction occurs

